---
title: Quick Ragu Fusilli with Mozzarella and Honey Dressed Leaves
description: Ragu is a slow cooked meat-based sauce that is traditionally served with pasta. We've sped it up a little in this tasty pasta bake, topped with mozzarella and served with delicate honey dressed leaves. Delicious!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/quick-ragu-fusilli-3a6b8b6d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/quick-ragu-fusilli-06e1bddc.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/quick-ragu-fusilli-59e486a3a5ed19049363bbf2
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: British
nutrition:
  calories: 932 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 87 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 60 g
  sodium: 2 g
  serving size: 753
---

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once hot,
add the @British beef mince{500%g} to the pan with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@black pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{5%minutes}. Break it up with a #wooden
spoon{}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{2} into half moons. Chop the
@celery stick{2} into small ½cm cubes. Put a large #saucepan{} of water on to
boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for the pasta.

Once the beef has browned, add the onion and celery. Cook until soft,
~{5%minutes}. Pour in the @tinned plum tomatoes{2%cans}, @beef stock pot{1}
and @Worcester sauce{3%tbsp}. Stir to dissolve the stock pot and break up the
tomatoes with a #spoon{}. Simmer until the ragu is thick and tomatoey,
~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @fusilli{360%g} (you don't need the whole pack!) to the
#pan{} of boiling water. Cook for ~{9%minutes} until al dente.

> Al dente simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of
> firmness left in the middle - if it's not quite there yet, just cook for a
> little longer.

Grate the @parmesan cheese{40%g}, thinly slice half the @mozzarella{2} and tear
the rest into small chunks. Chop the @cucumber{1} into 1cm chunks. Squeeze a
little @lemon{1} juice into a large #bowl{} and add the @honey{2%tbsp} and
@olive oil{2%tbsp} (amount specified in the ingredient list). Season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{} and mix together with a spoon. Preheat your #grill{}
to high.

Once the ragu has thickened and the pasta is cooked, drain the pasta in a
#colander{} and add it to the ragu. Add half the parmesan and the mozzarella
chunks. Stir together. Transfer the mixture to an #ovenproof dish{} (or leave
it in the pan if it's ovenproof), sprinkle over the remaining parmesan and lay
the mozzarella slices on top. Pop under your grill until golden and bubbly,
~{5%minutes}.

Add the @baby leaves{1%bag} and cucumber to the dressing and toss to combine.
Serve the fusilli ragu in #bowls{} with the honey dressed leaves on top. Enjoy!